Access point in my living room, same location as boulette or carton...

The wifi here is in managed mode, but the LAN ports run mesh
software ([[configuration/babel]] and [[configuration/batman]]). The uplink port is simply a DHCP client, so that it can connect to a regular internet uplink and announce it on the mesh. Otherwise it can network multiple mesh nodes through the gigabit LAN ports.

Those are the configuration steps followed:

 * [[configuration/flashing]] - with genb's firmware ([[guide complet|guides/install+node+facile]])
 * [[configuration/batman]] and [[configuration/babel]] - only on LAN ports, not on wifi
 * [[configuration/ip]] - regular IPv4 and IPv6, although wifi has a `192.168.1.1` net
 * [[configuration/services]] - IPv6, DHCP, DNS

Not documented: the access point is in managed mode, see the configuration dump below for examples.

